answers.body_markdown:
    x[n]=b[n]/A[n,n];

This is not the proper syntax for indexing a 2D array.  The `,` here is actually the comma operator, which discards the left operand and evaluates to the right operand, so `A[n,n]` is the same as `A[n]`.  So then you&#39;re attempting to assign a 1D array of `float` to a `float` which is the error you&#39;re getting.

What you want is:

    x[n]=b[n]/A[n][n];

Do the same for other references of `A`.

